    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-21T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-21T16:00:00-05:00" n="221"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1418: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative of the President</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-21T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 21, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>39. I have received the following telegram from Braden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“For your advice and with request that you please inform Licenciado
                            Zúñiga Montúfar, Dr. Rodríguez states that he will depart in a few days
                            for Caracas on Embassy affairs and he will there decide date of
                            departure for San José in agreement with Venezuelan Chancellery.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Ocheltree informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
